<font color="#FF0000">ANMESTY-ANOTHER PHONY GAME</font><br>
<tt>Sun Feb 16 20:40:07 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
Has anyone here witnessed the flood, the returning exodus of returning draft resistors when the amnesty program was offered?  Was there miles of cars at the Canadian Border checkpoints?  Were the airports packed?  Nope.  Most of those who &quot;cut and ran&quot; (your words Arthur) found out that &quot;life goes on outside all-around&quot;, in other words, Canada could be just as nice as America, and by the time the amnesty was offered, I believe only a few 100 if that many, who bothered to sign up. Personally I still know dozens who call Canada home, and even now, 30 years later, CHOOSE to not want to be citizens of the USA.  That's pretty strong conviction.   <br><br>
Anmesty was just another political game by our beloved political leaders.  This time it was to INVALIDATE the protestors.  To make them atone for their sin of standing up to the McNamara-LBJ-Nixon-Madness and refusing to die in the rice paddies.To give them a chance to crawl home and beg for American forgiveness.  Most of the draft resistors ignored it. <br><br>
I think we waste our time and posts on the amnesty issue here. It is just one more piece of crap, like the invention of body counts so Ma and Pa Kettle would watch the evening news a bit longer to &quot;get the score&quot; and see who was ahead, who killed more on that particular night.<br><br>
Arthur - your hell is your own invention, fueled by lies, deceptions, and the trust you had in your government. Your government abandoned you the first day you went in country. It was your fellow soldiers that kept you alive, not your government.    I don't understand how you can get upset about someone breaking the law when the entire viet nam tragedy was the ultimate lawless act.  Listen to Tom Dier and doc del, they have the viewpoint from the bush. I just have the viewpoint of the resistor.  But like us all, we are all brothers and survivors of a generation betrayed.<br><br>
Will we forever fight among ourselves, or will we grow and realize the truth, that we were set up and had, perhaps when we stop our own in fighting, we might just become a force for change.  Now, that's a concept that I bet the boys in the bund, I mean congress, don't want to see happen soon..<br><br>
doc
